text: What century is this set in? "Make babies"? Greece's population is only like 10 million. South Korea is just as small and has over 50 million. Greeks DON'T have big families these days. Everyone used to 100 years ago, Irish, Italians, Poles, Germans - but now you're lucky if a couple has one child. I know it's a comedy - but unfortunately, the 'traditions' and stereotypes shown aren't really true anymore. Modern Greeks are as 'Westernized' as everyone else. text: Well, I liked the movie, it was very funny! My great uncles live in the USA and I know they are more like these people in the movie than a regular family in Greece. But the only objection I have is the lamb. I mean really, every time I hear non Greeks talking about Greeks, they think we only eat lamb! Well, souvlaki is pork, gyro is pork, most of the steaks are pork. We also eat veal etc. But the most families I know eat lamb only in Easter and maybe 3-4 more times a year. Just saying...
